# User skills (`~/.agents/skills`)

All agent skills—including **shadcn** and **frontend-design**—live under **`~/.agents/skills/<name>/`**. The repo exposes them as **`web/.agents/skills-global`** after `bun run link:agents-skills` (gitignored symlink).

## When to use

If the user’s task matches a **skill name** below (or anything under `~/.agents/skills/`), **read `SKILL.md`** in that folder **before** improvising:

- **Paths (pick one):**
  - `~/.agents/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`
  - `web/.agents/skills-global/<skill-name>/SKILL.md` — only after running `bash web/bin/link-user-agents-skills.sh` (creates a gitignored symlink).

## Known skills (examples)

`shadcn`, `frontend-design`, `tdd`, `find-skills`, `write-a-prd`, `prd-to-plan`, `prd-to-issues`, `design-an-interface`, `request-refactor-plan`, `improve-codebase-architecture`, `triage-issue`, `git-guardrails-claude-code`, `setup-pre-commit`, `scaffold-exercises`, `migrate-to-shoehorn`, `grill-me`, `edit-article`, `obsidian-vault`, `ubiquitous-language`, `write-a-skill`, and others present on disk under `~/.agents/skills/`.

## How to load

Use the Read tool on the concrete `SKILL.md` path. Follow that skill’s instructions for the rest of the task.
